16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 The Legislature finds that it had the authority to enact the
20 provisions of the "February 2021 Regulated Utility Consumer
21 Protection Act" (hereinafter "the Act"). The Legislature finds that
22 cities and towns of the state have imposed certain franchise fees on
23 the securitization revenue stream which is required for defeasance
24 of the obligations issued by the Oklahoma Development Finance
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1220 Page 1

1 Auth ority pursuant to the Act. The Legislature finds that the
2 purpose of the Act was a matter of statewide concern and not a
3 matter of purely local or municipal concern. The Legislature finds
4 that certain municipalities have imposed franchise fees on the
5 securitization revenue stream contrary to legislative intent. The
6 Legislature finds that municipalities have imposed certain local
7 taxes upon the securitization revenue stream contrary to legislative
8 intent.
9 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
10 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9083 of Title 74, unless there
11 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
12 A. No municipality shall impose any franchise fee upon or with
13 respect to the securitization revenue stream required pursuant to
14 the provisions of the Act, any bond indenture related to the
15 obligations issued by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority
16 pursuant to the Act, or any order of the Oklahoma Corporation
17 Commission authorizing an affected public utility to impose charges
18 which constitute the securitization revenue stream to defease the
19 obligations issued by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority
20 pursuant to the Act.
21 B. The provisions of this section shall be applicable to the
22 securitization revenue stream for bonds or other obligations issued
23 by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority as described in
24 subsection A of this section and shall also be applicable to the
