6 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9084 of Title 74, unless there
8 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. No municipality shall impose any sales tax, use tax or any
10 other tax authorized pursuant to the provisions of Section 2701 et
11 seq. of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes on or with respect to the
12 securitization revenue stream for bonds or other obligations issued
13 by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority as described in
14 subsection A of Section 2 of this act.
15 B. The provisions of this section shall be applicable to the
16 securitization revenue stream for bonds or other obligations issued
17 by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority pursuant to the Act
18 and shall also be applicable to the securitization revenue stream
19 for any bonds or other obligations issued by the Oklahoma
